 {"id":"bd-3uqg.3.4","title":"[PROVIDER-NATIVE] Implement SAP AI Core provider integration","description":"Integrate sap-ai-core provider path including service-key/token handling and deployment/resource options with deterministic request routing.","acceptance_criteria":"1) SAP AI Core integration supports required auth and endpoint semantics. 2) Unit/contract tests cover protocol mapping, tool-call normalization, and failure classification. 3) E2E script with structured logs/transcripts proves end-to-end behavior and triage readiness.","notes":"Progress (FuchsiaBasin): implemented SAP service-key token exchange helper in auth flow (exchange_sap_access_token), added SAP ad-hoc model routing in models (v2/inference/deployments/<model>/chat/completions), and wired startup fallback in main to auto-exchange SAP token on MissingApiKey. Added focused unit tests for token exchange and SAP ad-hoc routing. Validation: cargo check --lib --bins passes. Full cargo check --all-targets, cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings, and cargo fmt --check currently fail due pre-existing unrelated provider module/test issues.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"FuchsiaBasin","owner":"FuchsiaBasin","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:15:19.576586012Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-10T08:28:12.559119858Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3uqg.3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-3uqg.2.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:22:32.175279769Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-3uqg.3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-3uqg.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:15:19.576586012Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-3uqg.3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-3uqg.7.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:22:32.683509452Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"bd-3uqg.3.5","title":"[PROVIDER-NATIVE] Implement GitLab Duo provider integration","description":"Integrate gitlab provider path (agentic chat/tool-calling semantics), including self-hosted instance URL overrides and auth mode handling.","acceptance_criteria":"1) gitlab provider path is integrated with canonical ID and auth semantics. 2) Unit tests cover request/response handling and failure surfaces. 3) E2E script and logs validate behavior and troubleshooting signals.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"TopazFalcon","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:15:19.623532739Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-10T08:35:16.322102333Z","closed_at":"2026-02-10T08:35:16.322009230Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3uqg.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-3uqg.2.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:22:32.891163731Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-3uqg.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-3uqg.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:15:19.623532739Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-3uqg.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-3uqg.7.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:22:33.096943316Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":965,"issue_id":"bd-3uqg.3.5","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"TopazFalcon: GitLab Duo provider implementation complete.

Created:
- src/providers/gitlab.rs: Full GitLabProvider implementing Provider trait
  - Proprietary GitLab Chat API format (NOT OpenAI-compatible)
  - POST to /api/v4/chat/completions with {content, additional_context}
  - Non-streaming: returns TextDelta + Done events from single response
  - Self-hosted base URL support (default: gitlab.com)
  - Bearer token auth (GITLAB_TOKEN / GITLAB_API_KEY)
  - 9 unit tests (defaults, builder, URL, request building, response deser)

Modified:
- src/providers/mod.rs: Added NativeGitlab variant, resolve_provider_route case, factory match arm
- tests/provider_backward_lock.rs: Added factory_routes_gitlab_native_provider test

Test results:
- 9/9 gitlab unit tests pass
- 2/2 factory dispatch tests pass
- 152/152 provider streaming tests pass (no regressions)
- cargo check --lib passes clean
- clippy clean for gitlab.rs (remaining errors are in bedrock.rs/copilot.rs from other agents)","created_at":"2026-02-10T08:35:09Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-3uqg.3.6","title":"[PROVIDER-NATIVE] Implement Cloudflare AI Gateway + Workers AI integrations","description":"Implement cloudflare-ai-gateway and cloudflare-workers-ai provider paths, including unified provider/model IDs, account/gateway config, and token auth behavior.","acceptance_criteria":"1) cloudflare AI gateway/workers integrations route correctly with expected auth/header handling. 2) Unit tests cover payload/event normalization and edge cases. 3) E2E scenario logs capture success/failure behavior for triage.","notes":"Claimed by RedCliff: implementing Cloudflare AI Gateway + Workers AI routing/metadata/tests; coordinating reservations via agent mail.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"RedCliff","owner":"RedCliff","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:15:19.665457028Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-10T08:29:37.288904141Z","closed_at":"2026-02-10T08:29:37.288872412Z","close_reason":"Implemented Cloudflare AI Gateway + Workers AI integration via OpenAI-compatible metadata/routing (canonical IDs, env-key mapping, factory dispatch tests, e2e env-name coverage). Targeted tests pass; full all-targets gates currently blocked by unrelated concurrent failures in src/providers/copilot.rs and tests/provider_backward_lock.rs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3uqg.3.6","depends_on_id":"bd-3uqg.2.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:22:33.290866984Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-3uqg.3.6","depends_on_id":"bd-3uqg.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:15:19.665457028Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-3uqg.3.6","depends_on_id":"bd-3uqg.7.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:22:33.484325495Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
